FT  11 JUL 94 / Business Travel (Update): Taiwan typhoon
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Typhoon Tim lashed eastern Taiwan with strong winds and heavy rain
yesterday, forcing the suspension of flights to two offshore islets.
Taiwanese officials said an important highway in Hualien city was closed
because of landslides set off by the torrential downpour.
In the Philippines, the Manila weather bureau said another tropical storm,
Vanessa, had developed in the South China Sea and was bringing strong winds
and heavy rains to the main Philippine island, Luzon.
