<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JUL 94 / Labour slams fall in training cash
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Government spending on training, enterprise and labour-market services has
fallen by more than a third in real terms since its peak in 1987-88, Mr Tony
Lloyd, Labour's training spokesman, said yester-day.
According to figures obtained through parliamentary questions, Pounds 4.3bn
was spent in 1987-88 at 1993 prices compared with Pounds 2.6bn in 1992-93.
Mr Lloyd said this showed that there had been a substantial cut in
resources, combined with a switch from spending on training to cheaper
schemes for the long-term unemployed.
