FT  11 JUL 94 / Takeovers 'good for shareholders'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The corporate takeovers of the 1980s benefited shareholders as well as
managements, a study yesterday from the Chartered Association of Certified
Accountants suggests.
The performance of companies that have been taken over has been
significantly above the level it would otherwise have been, three
researchers from Essex University concluded.
