<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JUL 94 / Companies plan to invest more
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Companies' investment intentions have risen in spite of tax increases, the
finance and leasing group Lombard Business Finance said.
Many economists see increased corporate investment as vital to re-balance
the economic recovery which has so far been fuelled by consumer spending.
In June, 63 per cent of companies surveyed planned to purchase a major asset
over the next three months, up from 61 per cent in March.
Companies are mainly investing to increase efficiency, rather than to expand
capacity, according to Lombard, while the proportion of companies saying
that the tax changes had caused them to cut investment plans was just 19 per
cent in June, down from 27 per cent in March.
</TEXT>
