FT  11 JUL 94 / Switch in demand for workers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Patterns of demand for temporary and permanent staff have diverged radically
over the past few years, Reed Personnel Services, the employment agency
group, said.
Demand for permanent staff outstripped temporary demand throughout the
1980s. However, during the recession the demand for temporary staff fell
less sharply than that for permanent staff.
In the last quarter the agency's index for temporary staff rose eight points
to 97, against the 1990 base level of 100. The permanent-staff index rose
seven points to 50.
