FT  09 JUL 94 / International Company News: US drug group sale
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
American Cyanamid, the US pharmaceuticals company, has agreed in principle
to sell its Davis &amp; Geck wound management business to its European joint
venture partner, B. Braun Melsungen of Germany, Reuter reports. Terms were
not disclosed.
Cyanamid said it would maintain its manufacturing operations in Puerto Rico.
The sale is subject to reaching definitive agreements and gaining government
approvals.
The two companies are partners in joint venture wound management companies
in Germany, Portugal and Spain. Under this agreement, B. Braun will acquire
Cyanamid's worldwide business, including surgical sutures and endoscopic
products.
Cyanamid said Davis &amp; Geck had 1993 sales of Dollars 300m.
