<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUL 94 / International Company News: Australia goldminers seek to
simplify link
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Samantha Gold, the small Western Australian gold-mining company, has made an
all-shares offer for Resolute Resources, another junior miner based in
Perth. The offer is worth around ADollars 350m (USDollars 255.5m).
Samantha is offering two of its own shares for every seven in Resolute. The
two companies have been linked since August last year, when Resolute
acquired control of Equity in Industry, which in turn held a large minority
stake in Samantha, making it the goldminer's largest shareholder.
This interest now stands at around 42 per cent of Samantha's equity, and the
bidder plans to buy back and eliminate that holding if the merger is
successful.
It said this simplification of the two groups' structures was a key reason
for the deal, although increased focus on gold and possible cost savings
were other factors. The merged group would have a forecast annual gold
production in excess of 300,000 ounces for fiscal 1995-96.
</TEXT>
