FT  09 JUL 94 / Finance and the Family: FT quarterly personal finance review
 -At a Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Investing some money overseas is not just a form of risk-spreading - it is
also a way of getting a stake in economies that appear to have strong
prospects for growth, and it allows investors to participate in industries
which do not exist at home.
The summer issue of the FT Quarterly Review of Personal Finance, to be
published with next Friday's paper and repeated with Saturday's, considers
the best ways of investing overseas - and where. The survey section of the
Review takes a critical look at Personal Pensions, in the light of recent
bad publicity.
