<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUL 94 / London Stock Exchange: Equity futures and options trading
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Increased fears on interest rates following the release of US employment
data brought a retreat to Footsie futures, though the contract closed off
the day's lows.
Trading in a 40 point range, the September contract on the FT-SE 100 hit a
high of 2,976 and a low of 2,937, before recovering to close at 2,959.
Volume at 12,511 showed a slight increase.
There was also an improvement in turnover in the traded options where the
closing total was 33,376 contracts. Tomkins, with 1,028 lots dealt, was the
busiest stock option.
