<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUL 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Demand for pepper in general has bee improving, despite the holiday season,
reports Man Producten. White pepper has become very scarce on the Europe
spot market with limited fresh supplies coming from producing countries. The
new Muntok crop has only just started and arrivals are still small. Prices
firmed up towards the end of the week as several shippers tried to cover
their July and August commitments. Muntok white faq, spot Rotterdam fetched
USDollars 2,950 a tonne, while July/August and August/September shipments
were at Dollars 2,850, cif. Black pepper prices remained steady, with spot
goods commanding a premium as stocks in Europe are diminishing. Black pepper
faq spot Rotterdam was at Dollars 1,700 a tonne, while grade 1 spot fetched
Dollars 1,775.
</TEXT>
