<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUL 94 / International Company News: Steady third-quarter result for
Laidlaw
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Better third-quarter results in the waste management, recycling and
transportation businesses of Laidlaw were slightly offset by a small decline
in hazardous waste operations. The company blamed this on landfill problems
in South Carolina and pressures on pricing.
Overall, Laidlaw, one of North America's top three waste management groups
and a Canadian Pacific associate, earned USDollars 38.9m, or 14 cents a
share, in the three months ended May 31. This compares to a 1992-93
third-quarter loss of Dollars 33.6m, or 12 cents, after a special Dollars
75m after-tax charge reflecting a write-down in the value of Laidlaw's
interest in ADT. Without the charge, the period showed net profit equal to
13 cents a share.
Third-quarter revenues this time were Dollars 579m, up 6.5 per cent. The
lower Canadian dollar reduced the total by Dollars 11.5m.
For the first nine months of fiscal 1994, overall net profit was USDollars
93.9m, or 34 cents a share, against USDollars 43.4m, or 16 cents in 1983.
</TEXT>
